post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_23188173_23188203_0": {"length": 17, "quality": 0.7391304347826086, "section_id": 3298}}, "n3337": {"so_23188173_23188203_0": {"length": 21, "quality": 0.9130434782608695, "section_id": 3168}}, "n4659": {"so_23188173_23188203_0": {"length": 12, "quality": 0.5217391304347826, "section_id": 4063}}}, "23188173": {"ViewCount": "54", "Body": "<p>Suppose I have the following class:</p>\n<pre><code>class dog\n{\n    public:\n    int age;\n    int bun;\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>Now this statement</p>\n<pre><code>dog d = {12,5}\n</code></pre>\n<p>would initialize <code>age</code> to 12 and <code>bun</code> to 5</p>\n<p>Now if the class above has a parameter-less constructor the above statement initialization does not work. I would appreciate it if someone could explain why that happens?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "23188203", "Title": "Aggregate initialization with regular constructor", "CreationDate": "2014-04-20T22:12:29.587", "Id": "23188173", "CommentCount": "0", "LastEditDate": "2014-04-21T00:15:29.947", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "420683", "LastActivityDate": "2014-04-21T00:15:29.947", "Score": "1", "OwnerUserId": "1305891", "Tags": "<c++><c++11>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "23188203": {"Id": "23188203", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>The syntax <code>dog d = { 12, 5 };</code> is <em>aggregate initialization</em> when the class <code>dog</code> is an aggregate. A user-provided constructor prevents a class from being an aggregate; cf. C++11 8.5.1/1:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_23188173_23188203_0\">An <em>aggregate</em> is an array or a class (Clause 9) with no user-provided constructors (12.1), no <em>brace-or-equal-initializers</em> for non-static data members (9.2), no private or protected non-static data members (Clause 11), no base classes (Clause 10), and no virtual functions (10.3).</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>(I believe that the next revision of C++ will permit brace-or-equals initializers in aggregates.)</p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "596781", "LastActivityDate": "2014-04-21T00:13:26.113", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2014-04-20T22:15:47.153", "ParentId": "23188173", "CommentCount": "2", "OwnerUserId": "596781", "LastEditDate": "2014-04-21T00:13:26.113"}});